blocks
(
    // SimpleGrading:
    // Values = 1: Generates uniformly sized cells in that direction.
    // Values > 1: Cells grow in size from the first vertex to the second vertex (e.g., (2 1 1)).
    // Values < 1: Cells shrink in size from the first vertex to the second vertex (e.g., (0.5 1 1)).
    // Consider a block with vertices defined from x = 0 (start) to x = 10 (end).
    // Uniform mesh: simpleGrading (1 1 1) results in evenly spaced cells across the entire block.
    // Refinement at the end: simpleGrading (5 1 1) makes the final cell at x = 10 exactly 5 times larger than the first cell at x = 0.
    // Refinement at the start: simpleGrading (0.2 1 1) (which is equivalent to 1/5) makes the cell at x = 10 five times larger than the first cell at x = 0, concentrating smaller cells at the origin.
    hex (0 1 4 3 9 10 13 12) (10 10 1) simpleGrading (2 2 1)
    hex (1 2 5 4 10 11 14 13) (10 10 1) simpleGrading (0.5 2 1)
    hex (3 4 7 6 12 13 16 15) (10 10 1) simpleGrading (2 0.5 1)
    hex (4 5 8 7 13 14 17 16) (10 10 1) simpleGrading (0.5 0.5 1)
);

